into an earth mound at the side of the road 
the syrians maintain 40000 troops in lebanon under a 1976 arab 
league peacekeeping mandate 
they control about 70 percent of the country and have long been 
targets for moslem rivals who seek to undermine their peacekeeping 
mission 
