president najib told his ruling 
communist party on sunday that it should surrender its monopoly on 
power and hold a special session to write the change into the 
constitution 
the announcement was made during a meeting of the central 
committee of the ruling peoples democratic party of afghanistan 
the meeting also debated changing the ruling partys name 
one choice favored by liberals was the national unity party 
another the peoples party was supported by hardliners no 
decision was made 
the party should take voluntary legal steps to cancel its 
privileged status najib said in a speech to the central 
committee according to the official bakhtar news agency we must 
give up our monopoly on power 
the meeting also removed 24 central committee members but this 
did not reduce the partys hold on power as its members retained 
control over all government ministries 
najibs speech was seen as an attempt to make himself and his 
party more acceptable to usbacked guerrilla groups which have 
been fighting his party more than a decade 
following the withdrawal of soviet troops last year the 
guerrillas said najib must step down before peace talks could begin 
afghan government officials said they interpreted najibs 
tentative steps toward political reforms as a sign of his weakness 
and perhaps of the soviet unions unwillingness to back largescale 
change in afghanistan 
the soviet union is afghanistans closest military and economic 
ally the central committee meeting was attended by highranking 
soviet diplomats and officials from the soviet foreign ministry 
afghan government officials said 
diplomats in kabul have said a march 6 coup attempt has brought 
najib to his weakest position since being installed as president in 
1986 a highranking government official said sunday that about 
half of the officers in the military are being replaced following 
the insurrection 
the coup attempt was led by shah nawz tanai who was defense 
minister at the time national security remains compromised because 
tanai escaped and joined forces with the guerrillas 
najib called for a meeting to modify references in afghanistans 
constitution to the guiding role the party plays in national 
affairs 
the national assembly meeting would be held within two months a 
government official said it would include representatives from 
afghanistans largely powerless national assembly along with 
appointed members from government ministries and important tribes 
around the country 
in spite of all our success war still continues and the 
people still suffer najib said but we have taken steps toward 
giving up the monopoly on power recently weve been going slowly 
we need to accelerate the trend toward democracy in our society 
