a mildmannered former consultant who 
authorities say killed his wife mother and three children and then 
lived quietly for 18 years under an assumed name now passes his 
time in his jail cell reading the bible 
lawyers for john e list and prosecutors meanwhile are busy 
preparing for trial starting tuesday and jockeying over whether a 
fivepage letter list left behind intended for his pastor can be 
used as evidence 
its been categorized over the years as a somewhat detailed 
diary of events said lt bernard tracy the latest in a long 
line of westfield detectives handling the case since 1971 
police believe that lists wife helen 45 his 85yearold 
mother alma and their children patricia 16 john jr 15 and 
