debut saturday with a performance of hector berlioz the 
trojans 
the teatro amazonas about 1700 miles northwest of rio de 
janeiro had been silent for most of the past 83 years fizzling 
with the end of the rubber boom 
after a 1907 performance the theater was mostly abandoned with 
only an occasional play or concert performed on its once glorious 
stage by the early 1980s time rain and termites had nearly 
destroyed the building 
the headtotoe renovation included a paint job for the pink 
pastel facade 36000 new tiles and a sound system 
more than 3000 gallons of insecticide were injected into the 
wood to prevent termites from eating the building a second time 
the legendary rise and fall of the teatro amazonas was the 
subject of german director werner herzogs movie fitzcarraldo 
